<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Succour1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Succour,</orth> subst. any kind of relief or assistance: <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.4.75" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 4, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.32" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.4.45" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 4, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 2, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.3.30" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.1.109" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 1, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.1.171" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 1, 171</bibl>. <cit><quote>far from his s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.261" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 261</bibl></cit> (from the possibility of coming to his assistance). <cit><quote>draw to her s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 5.4.55" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 55</bibl></cit>. Plur. <emph>--s</emph> == auxiliary troops: <bibl n="shak. h5 3.3.45" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 3, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.4.23" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 4, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.285" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 285</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>